#: tools/mate-session-inhibit.c:118
#, c-format
msgid ""
"%s [OPTION...] COMMAND\n"
"\n"
"Execute COMMAND while inhibiting some session functionality.\n"
"\n"
"  -h, --help        Show this help\n"
"  --version         Show program version\n"
"  --app-id ID       The application id to use\n"
"                    when inhibiting (optional)\n"
"  --reason REASON   The reason for inhibiting (optional)\n"
"  --inhibit ARG     Things to inhibit, colon-separated list of:\n"
"                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount\n"
"\n"
"If no --inhibit option is specified, idle is assumed.\n"
msgstr ""
"%s [INSTELLEN …] OORDER\n"
"\n"
"De OORDER utföhren un daarbi eenige Törn-Funktioonen unnerdrücken.\n"
"\n"
"  -h, --help        Deese Hülp wiesen\n"
"  --version         Programm-Versioon wiesen\n"
"  --app-id ID       De Anwennens-ID, wat bi’m Unnerdrücken\n"
"                    bruukt worden sall (wenn du willst)\n"
"  --reason GRUND    De Grund för dat Unnerdrücken (wenn du willst)\n"
"  --inhibit ARG     Dingen tum Unnerdrücken; Dübbelpunkt-trennte List vun:\n"
"                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount\n"
"\n"
"Wenn keene »--inhibit«-Instellen angeven is, word »idle« annohmen.\n"

